en: We'll begin with the start-up sequence.
fr: Nous allons commencer par la sequence de demarrage.

en: Wait for the engines to spool up.
The engines are now supplying power.  We can turn off the APU.
fr: Les moteurs fournissent maintenant de l'energie. Nous pouvons desactiver l'APU.

en: Slowly lift the throttle until you take off.
fr: Soulevez lentement la manette des gaz jusqu'a ce que vous decolliez.

en: Try to keep your nose level with the horizon.
fr: Essayez de garder votre nez au niveau de l'horizon.

en: Adjust throttle to maintain zero vertical speed.
fr: Reglez l'accelerateur pour maintenir une vitesse verticale nulle.

en: Cancel lateral speed by rolling or pitching slightly in the opposite direction.
fr: Annulez la vitesse laterale en roulant ou en tangant legerement dans la direction opposee.

en: Try to hold this position for a few moments.
fr: Essayez de maintenir cette position pendant quelques instants.

en: Adjust throttle to slowly descend at about -6 m/s
fr: Reglez les gaz pour descendre lentement a environ -6 m/s

Description: Name of a legacy tutorial objective

en: Welcome to the Vertical Flight autopilot training.
fr: Bienvenue a la formation de pilote automatique Vertical Flight.

en: Vertical flight can be tricky, but by using the AP, you will be a master in no time.
First, make sure the engines are tilted at 90 degrees.
fr: make sure the engines are tilted at 90 degrees.

en: First, make sure the engines are tilted at 90 degrees.
fr: make sure the engines are tilted at 90 degrees.

en: The HVR mode will assist you in staying upright and keeping your horizontal velocity under control.
fr: Le mode HVR vous aidera a rester debout et a garder votre vitesse horizontale sous contr�le.

en: The ALT mode will take control of the engines and convert inputs into climb or descent rates.
fr: Le mode ALT prendra le contr�le des moteurs et convertira les entrees en taux de montee ou de descente.

en: Keeping your throttle centered will hold a hover
fr: Garder votre manette des gaz centree tiendra un vol stationnaire

en: Raise or lower the throttle to climb or descend
fr: Augmenter ou abaisser la manette des gaz pour monter ou descendre

en: Keep your left thumb away from the tilt control.
fr: eloignez votre pouce gauche de la commande d'inclinaison.

en: Any engine tilt less than 90 will disengage HVR AP
fr: Toute inclinaison du moteur inferieure a 90 desengagera le HVR AP

en: Lift throttle now.  Climb to {50} altitude.
Now set your throttle lever to the midpoint to hover.
You should now be in a stable hover
fr: Vous devriez maintenant etre en vol stationnaire stable

en: You can make adjustments to the throttle to climb or descend as needed.
fr: Vous pouvez faire des ajustements a la manette des gaz pour monter ou descendre selon vos besoins.

en: Now you can use the joystick to move around
fr: Vous pouvez maintenant utiliser le joystick pour vous deplacer

en: The HVR autopilot will handle attitude control
fr: Le pilote automatique HVR gerera le contr�le d'attitude

en: You just have to tilt the joystick in the direction you want to go
fr: Il vous suffit d'incliner le joystick dans la direction o� vous voulez aller

en: You can also twist the joystick to yaw
fr: Vous pouvez egalement tordre le joystick pour lacet

en: As you move around, study how the AP handles the vehicle
fr: study how the AP handles the vehicle

en: Let's try flying into some targets.
fr: Essayons de voler dans certaines cibles.

en: Great! Now lets try to land back on the helipad.
Bring yourself to a stop by centering the throttle, and steering the stick in the opposite direction as your horizontal velocity indicator.
fr: and steering the stick in the opposite direction as your horizontal velocity indicator.

en: Rotate to face towards the helipads.
fr: Tournez pour faire face aux heliports.

en: Begin to move towards the pad.  Adjust your altitude control and steer so your velocity vector is pointed just above the pad.
fr: Commencez a vous deplacer vers le pad.�Ajustez votre contr�le d'altitude et dirigez de sorte que votre vecteur de vitesse soit pointe juste au-dessus du pad.

en: Slow your forward speed and rate of descent.
fr: Ralentissez votre vitesse d'avancement et votre taux de descente.

en: Adjust rate of descent to bring it down gently.
fr: Ajustez le taux de descente pour le faire descendre doucement.

en: Touch down!  Throttle down and enable brake locks.
fr: Atterrir!�Reduisez les gaz et activez le verrouillage des freins.

en: Congratulations!  Next time: Manual vertical flight and transitioning.
fr: Toutes nos felicitations!�La prochaine fois : Vol vertical manuel et transition.

Description: Name of a legacy tutorial objective

en: Welcome to the basic weapons tutorial.
fr: Bienvenue dans le didacticiel des armes de base.

en: Today, we will be covering weapon configuration, target acquisition, and firing weapons.
fr: we will be covering weapon configuration

en: Let's start by setting the MFDs to the pages we will use.
fr: Commen�ons par regler les MFD sur les pages que nous utiliserons.

en: The EQUIP page shows what you have on each of the vehicle's equipment mounts.
fr: La page EQUIP montre ce que vous avez sur chacun des supports d'equipement du vehicule.

en: It displays information on each item, and allows you to arm/disarm, configure, or mark them for jettison.
We'll go over each feature in more detail later.
fr: Nous reviendrons sur chaque fonctionnalite plus en detail plus tard.

en: The TGP is what you will use to acquire ground targets.
fr: Le TGP est ce que vous utiliserez pour acquerir des cibles au sol.

en: To use it, first you must supply power to the sensor mounted under the nose of the vehicle.
fr: first you must supply power to the sensor mounted under the nose of the vehicle.

en: The TGP will be in FWD mode by default, which just looks straight forward.
To be able to control it, you must designate the TGP as the sensor of interest (SOI).
fr: you must designate the TGP as the sensor of interest (SOI).

en: Now, you can slew the targeting sensor around using the thumb control on your joystick.
fr: you can slew the targeting sensor around using the thumb control on your joystick.

en: Try slewing the TGP around using the joystick thumb control.
fr: Essayez de faire pivoter le TGP a l'aide de la commande au pouce du joystick.

en: When you move the sensor, it will auto switch to TGT mode, which locks its focus point on the ground while you're flying.
fr: it will auto switch to TGT mode

en: The yellow arrow on the screen shows the relative bearing to the target point.
fr: La fleche jaune a l'ecran indique le relevement relatif par rapport au point cible.

en: The target point also shows up on the NAV map as a yellow cross.
fr: Le point cible appara�t egalement sur la carte NAV sous la forme d'une croix jaune.

en: Now let's find some targets.  Take off and fly to the objective waypoint.
fr: Trouvons maintenant quelques cibles.�Decollez et volez jusqu'au waypoint objectif.

en: Now that we are in the AO, you can enable the Master Arm switch.
fr: you can enable the Master Arm switch.

en: With the weapon system armed, you will see some new icons on the HUD
fr: you will see some new icons on the HUD

en: At the center, you have the weapon targeting reticle or pipper.
fr: you have the weapon targeting reticle or pipper.

en: Here, you have weapon type, name, and shots remaining.
You can cycle through all ARMED weapons by pressing the button on the joystick.
fr: Vous pouvez faire defiler toutes les armes ARMeES en appuyant sur le bouton du joystick.

en: These unguided weapons can be fired by simply pulling the trigger on the joystick.
fr: Ces armes non guidees peuvent etre tirees en appuyant simplement sur la g�chette du joystick.

en: You have limited stores so save your rounds for the targets.
Let's try deploying the GAU-8 on some ground targets.
fr: Essayons de deployer le GAU-8 sur certaines cibles au sol.

en: In a moment, you'll receive a mission objective.
You can auto-slew your TGP to the objective waypoint by pressing the WPT button in the TGP screen.
fr: Vous pouvez orienter automatiquement votre TGP vers le waypoint objectif en appuyant sur le bouton WPT dans l'ecran TGP.

en: Go ahead and destroy the tanks.
Great job!  Now let's work with rockets.
fr: Bon travail!�Travaillons maintenant avec les fusees.

en: By default, each pull of the trigger will fire one rocket.
fr: each pull of the trigger will fire one rocket.

en: However, they can be configured to launch rapidly.  This is called 'ripple' firing.
fr: they can be configured to launch rapidly.  This is called 'ripple' firing.

en: To access a weapons config menu, set the EQUIP MFD page to CONFIG mode
fr: set the EQUIP MFD page to CONFIG mode

en: Then, select the weapon you want to configure.
fr: select the weapon you want to configure.

en: If you have multiple of the same weapon, the settings will be copied over to all of them.
fr: the settings will be copied over to all of them.

en: Try setting the rockets to different ripple intervals and destroy the next set of targets.
fr: Essayez de regler les roquettes a differents intervalles d'ondulation et detruisez la prochaine serie de cibles.

en: Well done! You've destroyed all of the targets.
fr: Bien fait!�Vous avez detruit toutes les cibles.

en: This concludes the basic weapons tutorial.
fr: Ceci conclut le didacticiel sur les armes de base.

Description: Name of a legacy tutorial objective

en: Welcome to the Basic Flight tutorial.
fr: Bienvenue dans le didacticiel Basic Flight.

en: We'll skip the start-up procedure now.
fr: Nous allons sauter la procedure de demarrage maintenant.

en: The main flight controls are the joystick and throttle.  You can grip them by holding the grip buttons, or toggle lock your hands to them by tapping the grip buttons.
fr: or toggle lock your hands to them by tapping the grip buttons.

en: To steer the front wheel, you will have to twist the joystick on the vertical axis.
fr: you will have to twist the joystick on the vertical axis.

en: In order to get moving, we need to tilt the engines to the forward position.
fr: we need to tilt the engines to the forward position.

en: Hold the throttle trigger to lock the brakes
fr: Maintenez la g�chette d'accelerateur pour verrouiller les freins

en: Then press and hold up on the throttle thumb control to tilt the engines forward.
If you release the brakes and slightly lift the throttle lever, you will start to roll.
Apply small amounts of throttle or brakes to control your speed.
fr: Appliquez de petites quantites d'accelerateur ou de freins pour contr�ler votre vitesse.

en: Full stop!  Throttle down and hold the throttle brake trigger.
fr: Arret complet!�Baissez les gaz et maintenez la g�chette de frein d'accelerateur.

en: Let's prepare for a conventional take-off.
Set the brake lock so you can free up your hands.
fr: Reglez le verrou de frein pour pouvoir liberer vos mains.
Reglez les volets sur le reglage 1.

en: Make sure all flight assists are enabled
fr: Assurez-vous que toutes les aides au vol sont activees

en: Check that the engines are tilted all the way forward.
fr: Verifiez que les moteurs sont inclines completement vers l'avant.

en: Now grab the throttle and hold the brakes...

fr: ... vous pouvez donc desactiver le blocage des freins.
Tournez maintenant a gauche sur la piste 20

en: Now.. to take off, raise the throttle to full and steer to keep aligned with the runway.
fr: raise the throttle to full and steer to keep aligned with the runway.

en: Speed up to [80]! Straight down the runway!
fr: Accelerez jusqu'a [80]�!�Tout droit sur la piste !

en: Now carefully rotate the joystick back to pull the nose up!
Now gently steer your nose to about 20 degrees and keep climbing to {1000} ASL.

fr: Pratiquons les commandes de vol de base.

en: Rotate the joystick left or right to roll towards your target
fr: Tournez le joystick vers la gauche ou la droite pour rouler vers votre cible

en: Rotate the joystick forward or back to pitch your nose towards it.
fr: Tournez le joystick vers l'avant ou l'arriere pour incliner votre nez vers lui.

en: This is your velocity vector, showing the direction you are moving.
fr: showing the direction you are moving.

en: You want to steer velocity vector towards where you want to go.
fr: Vous voulez diriger le vecteur vitesse vers l'endroit o� vous voulez aller.

en: Great flying! Now let's try to land at the airbase.
fr: Super vol !�Essayons maintenant d'atterrir sur la base aerienne.

en: Start your landing here at about [150]
Line up with the runway and bring speed down to about [100]
fr: Alignez-vous avec la piste et reduisez la vitesse a environ [100]

en: Flaps down, gear down.  Speed down to [80]
Maintain speed and glide slope.  Keep the vector on target!
fr: Maintenir la vitesse et la pente de descente.�Gardez le vecteur sur la cible�!

en: Prepare to flare nose up for a smooth landing
fr: Preparez-vous a arrondir le nez pour un atterrissage en douceur

en: Touch down! Bring your nose down.
Steer down the runway, throttle down and carefully apply brakes.
fr: throttle down and carefully apply brakes.

en: Congratulations!  This concludes the basic flight tutorial.
fr: Toutes nos felicitations!�Ceci conclut le didacticiel de vol de base.

Description: Short description of playable vehicle AH-94
en: The AH-94 "Dragonfly" is a twin-turboshaft attack helicopter with a tandem cockpit for two pilots.
Help make preparations to defend the island. Transport personnel to coastal SAM site.
fr: Aidez a faire des preparatifs pour defendre l'�le.�Transporter le personnel vers le site SAM c�tier.

en: Let the soldiers into your passenger bay.
fr: Laissez les soldats entrer dans votre compartiment passagers.

en: Drop the soldiers off at the east bay SAM site.
fr: Deposez les soldats sur le site SAM de la baie est.

en: Join up with the fighter escort wing.

fr: Enqueter sur le site du crash de l'AV-42.

en: Pick up the survivors from the crash site.
fr: Ramassez les survivants sur le site du crash.

en: Deliver the survivors to the hospital.
Return to and land at the airbase.
fr: Retournez et atterrissez a la base aerienne.

en: Allow the fighters to clear out the hostile drones.
fr: Permettez aux combattants d'eliminer les drones hostiles.

en: Destroy the drone ships laying mines on supply routes.
fr: Detruisez les drones posant des mines sur les routes de ravitaillement.

en: Meet up with Victor1 at the waypoint.
Lead the strike group to the area of operations.
fr: Dirigez le groupe d'intervention jusqu'a la zone d'operations.
[Critique] Detruisez les bateaux de la mine.

en: If able, support your wingmen by destroying the carrier's weapons and drones.
fr: support your wingmen by destroying the carrier's weapons and drones.

en: Join the carrier fleet embarking on a pre-emptive naval strike.
fr: Rejoignez la flotte de porte-avions et lancez-vous dans une attaque navale preventive.

en: Search for the lost pilot near the objective waypoint.
fr: Recherchez le pilote perdu pres du waypoint objectif.

en: Lead the lost pilot to the refuel tanker.
fr: Menez le pilote perdu jusqu'au ravitailleur.
Laissez le pilote faire le plein.

en: Lead the pilot to the aircraft carrier.
Meet the enemy in open water for a pre-emptive strike.
fr: Rencontrez l'ennemi en eau libre pour une frappe preventive.

en: Help defend the fleet from the incoming drones.
fr: Aidez a defendre la flotte contre les drones entrants.

en: Destroy or disable all enemy weapon systems, sensors, and drones.
Return to the fleet and land.
fr: Retournez a la flotte et atterrissez.

en: Return to the island to investigate why communications have gone silent.
fr: Retournez sur l'�le pour decouvrir pourquoi les communications sont devenues silencieuses.

en: Take off and fly to the aerial fuel tanker.
fr: Decollage et vol vers le petrolier aerien.
Laissez votre Romeo1-1 faire le plein.

en: Allow Romeo1-2 to refuel. Then you may refuel yourself if necessary.
Avoid the enemy fleet. Return to the waypoint and await orders.
fr: evitez la flotte ennemie.�Retournez au waypoint et attendez les ordres.

en: Destroy the armored units moving toward our allied infantry.
fr: Detruisez les unites blindees qui se dirigent vers notre infanterie alliee.

en: Begin a counterattack under the cover of darkness.
fr: Commencez une contre-attaque sous le couvert de l'obscurite.

en: Take off and prepare for your anti-ship strike.
fr: Decollez et preparez-vous a votre greve anti-navire.

en: Destroy the long range missile cruiser.
fr: Detruisez le croiseur lance-missiles a longue portee.

en: Begin to take back the island and eliminate the enemy fleet off the northern coast.
fr: Commencez a reprendre l'�le et eliminez la flotte ennemie au large de la c�te nord.

en: Destroy the incoming enemy carrier fleet.
fr: Detruisez la flotte de porte-avions ennemie entrante.

en: Clear out the enemy units at the airbase.
fr: eliminez les unites ennemies a la base aerienne.

en: Destroy the enemy SAM site to allow reinforcements to take off.
fr: Detruisez le site SAM ennemi pour permettre aux renforts de decoller.

en: Rearm if necessary, then regroup with Victor 1.
Destroy the rocket-equipped drone boats threatening the carrier.
fr: Detruisez les drones equipes de fusees mena�ant le porte-avions.

en: Destroy the carrier group's radars and air defenses so bombers can come to help.
fr: Detruisez les radars et les defenses antiaeriennes du groupe de porte-avions pour que les bombardiers puissent venir en aide.

en:
Negotiations for peace have failed.  We believe the enemy will strike here first, as a stepping stone to the mainland.

We have begun preparing coastal air defenses.
fr: as a stepping stone to the mainland.

en:
As an AV-42C pilot, you will deliver personnel to the defense sites.

Other pilots and soldiers will be arriving by air from the mainland soon.
fr: you will deliver personnel to the defense sites.

en: As we continue to prepare our defenses against the invasive enemy forces, we need to secure supply routes from the mainland to the island.
fr: we need to secure supply routes from the mainland to the island.

en: The troops you recovered from the crash site reported that they spotted what seemed to be unmanned vessels deploying sea mines near the south east supply route.
fr: Les troupes que vous avez recuperees sur le site de l'ecrasement ont signale avoir repere ce qui semblait etre des navires sans pilote deployant des mines marines pres de la route d'approvisionnement sud-est.

en:
You will lead a strike group with the order of destroying all hostile targets in the designated area.  

Prepare your aircraft appropriately.
fr: Vous dirigerez un groupe d'attaque avec l'ordre de detruire toutes les cibles hostiles dans la zone designee.

en: Our engineers were able to salvage the navigation computers from the drone ships and used them to determine the location of the main naval fleet of the enemy.
fr: Nos ingenieurs ont pu recuperer les ordinateurs de navigation des navires drones et les ont utilises pour determiner l'emplacement de la principale flotte navale de l'ennemi.

en: We have tasked an aircraft carrier fleet to intercept before they get too close to the island.  In order to maximize their force, you and other pilots are ordered to join the fleet.
fr: you and other pilots are ordered to join the fleet.

en: A pilot belonging to the carrier was out on combat air patrol when his navigation systems experienced a failure.  The pilot is lost and low on fuel, so you must quickly find him and lead him to the fuel tanker on the way to the carrier.
fr: so you must quickly find him and lead him to the fuel tanker on the way to the carrier.

en: We have intercepted the enemy fleet sooner than we expected to. They have already deployed aerial drones which are heading towards our fleet. All units are to scramble to defend the fleet, as well as quickly launch a counter-attack.
fr: as well as quickly launch a counter-attack.

en:
The enemy force is numerous and includes small drone boats, missile cruisers, and drone carriers. This is going to get messy.

Good luck.

We received an encrypted message from the island airbase which suggested that a large presence was detected coming in from the north.

After that, all communications went silent.
fr: Nous avons re�u un message crypte de la base aerienne de l'�le qui suggerait qu'une forte presence avait ete detectee en provenance du nord.

en:
The captain is worried that the enemy fleet we just attacked was just a diversion, and a larger enemy fleet somehow sailed to the island undetected.

We are returning to the island to investigate the radio silence.
fr: and a larger enemy fleet somehow sailed to the island undetected.

en:
We are conserving on-board jet fuel in anticipation of responding to the potential threat, so the fighter escorts will need to refuel in the air.

Once everyone is topped off, scout the island and report back.  Good luck.
fr: so the fighter escorts will need to refuel in the air.

en:
On the scouting sortie, a large enemy fleet was detected north of the island.  The enemy has also begun landing ground units on the island.

Before we can begin to move in and take back the island, we need to eliminate the threat posed by the enemy long range missile cruiser.
fr: a large enemy fleet was detected north of the island.  The enemy has also begun landing ground units on the island.

en: The cruiser has an array of launch tubes which we believe are capable of deploying two-stage surface-to-air and anti-ship missiles.  It also has a vertical launching system defense cannons, so it may not be effective to use conventional bombs or air-to-ground missiles.
fr: so it may not be effective to use conventional bombs or air-to-ground missiles.

en: In order to take out the threat, we are authorizing the use of the AGM-89 anti-ship cruise missile.  It has advanced features such as waypoint navigation, radar target acquisition, and a large payload.  Use it wisely and destroy the high priority target.
fr: we are authorizing the use of the AGM-89 anti-ship cruise missile.  It has advanced features such as waypoint navigation

en:
The mission launches at midnight. You will be escorted by a small wing of fighters to defend you from airborne threats.

The enemy has likely deployed more self-propelled SAM units to the island, so keep an eye out for missile launches and radar locks.

Good luck.
fr: La mission demarre a minuit.�Vous serez escorte par une petite escadre de chasseurs pour vous defendre des menaces aeriennes.

en:
With the destruction of the enemy fleet's most powerful ship, we can begin an effort to take back the island.

Through the night, the enemy has continued to deploy troops and set up defenses around the island.
fr: we can begin an effort to take back the island.

en:
The first order is to clear out enemy units from the island airbase. Air defenses have been set up, so be prepared to use the surrounding hills for cover.

Once the airbase has been cleared, we can use it for refueling and rearming.
fr: so be prepared to use the surrounding hills for cover.

en:
Once that is out of the way, we must eliminate the rest of the enemy fleet parked off the norther coast.

An allied carrier fleet is arriving from the east to support us, but are unable to launch aircraft due to enemy air defenses in the eastern city.
fr: we must eliminate the rest of the enemy fleet parked off the norther coast.

en:
Destroy the eastern air defenses to allow the allied pilots to take off, then make a combined effort to destroy the enemy fleet.

The allied fleet will also move into firing range to support with anti-ship missiles.
fr: then make a combined effort to destroy the enemy fleet.

en: Quick flights and practice scenarios for the AV-42C.
fr: Vols rapides et scenarios d'entra�nement pour l'AV-42C.

en: Free flight on a custom map.
fr: Vol libre sur une carte personnalisee.

en: Practice refueling in the air. Remember to lower your starting fuel.
fr: Entra�nez-vous a faire le plein en l'air.�N'oubliez pas de baisser votre carburant de demarrage.

en: Practice landing on the carrier or one of the cruisers.

en:
Several enemy air, land, and naval units are scattered around the island.
Complete each of the mission objectives and return to the carrier.
You may need to return to the carrier to refuel and rearm during the mission.

Destroy tanks threatening the raid team.

en:
You are stationed at our most remote airbase, closest to the enemy border.

The enemy seeks to destroy the airbase's supplies in order to prevent us from conducting airstrikes in this region.

Intel has revealed that the enemy has launched a multi-pronged effort to attack the airbase.

A small group of hostile self-propelled artillery have mobilized to get into firing range of our supply depots.
fr: Intel a revele que l'ennemi a lance un effort sur plusieurs fronts pour attaquer la base aerienne.

en:
While it will be necessary to destroy the artillery, we believe that the attack is aimed to distract us from a follow-up airstrike.

The type of attackers, their locations, and numbers are unknown at this time.
fr: we believe that the attack is aimed to distract us from a follow-up airstrike.

en:
An E-4 AWACS will be deployed in order to aid in locating the airborne threats.

Due to our proximity to enemy territory, the AWACS will be vulnerable.  Please defend it if necessary.
fr: Un E-4 AWACS sera deploye afin d'aider a localiser les menaces aeriennes.

en:
SUMMARY:
Objective:
Defend airbase supply depots.

Known targets:
3x self-propelled artillery

Unknown targets:
Bombers and/or attack aircraft.

Now's our chance to head back out and return the favor to the enemy.

They occupy two airbases -- one to the northeast, and one further due north.
fr: C'est maintenant notre chance de repartir et de rendre la pareille a l'ennemi.

en:
You must destroy the 4 supply depots at each base, for a total of 8 targets.

The enemy is most likely expecting us, so they probably beefed up air defenses as well as numerous aircraft on patrol.

Use the cover of darkness and terrain to mask your approach to the targets.

We have gathered intel on the near exact locations of their supplies, which will be set as the objective waypoints.

How you want to attack is up to you.
I recommend to remain radar silent to avoid detection.
fr: which will be set as the objective waypoints.

en:
SUMMARY:
Objective: 
- Destroy the 8 supply depots at each base (4 each).

Threats:
- Numerous radar and IR SAM sites
- Hostile combat air patrol

You've been transferred to the airbase near Gloom Lake.  

This lake lies on another border between our nation and the enemy's, and is where they conduct tests on naval vessels and aircraft.
fr: Vous avez ete transfere a la base aerienne pres de Gloom Lake.

en:
There have been an unusually high number of enemy drones harassing us recently.  They fly dangerously close to our base and force us to take defensive measures.  

We believe that they're attempting to distract us while they test new military technologies.
fr: Il y a eu un nombre inhabituellement eleve de drones ennemis nous harcelant recemment.�Ils volent dangereusement pres de notre base et nous obligent a prendre des mesures defensives.

en:
In order to put a damper on their research efforts, we're sending out a group of F/A-26Bs configured to sink their test ships.

Although this is a testing area, the enemy ships are fully functional and armed.
fr: we're sending out a group of F/A-26Bs configured to sink their test ships.

en:
You and your wingmen are tasked to destroy enemy air defenses and patrol aircraft, to allow the strikers to perform the anti-shipping attack.

The strikers will be in the air waiting for you.  Join them and escort them along their attack path.
fr: to allow the strikers to perform the anti-shipping attack.

en:
When you reach the end of the attack path, the strikers will begin anti-shipping. Target radars to prevent them from defending against the attack.

Simultaneously, allied combat air patrol will be vectored to the area to help keep enemy aircraft away.
fr: the strikers will begin anti-shipping. Target radars to prevent them from defending against the attack.

en:
SUMMARY:
Objective: Support strikers while they attack enemy ships.
- Suppress enemy air defenses
- Defend strikers from enemy air patrols

Primary Targets:
- Radars
- Aggressive Aircraft

Threats:
- Ships
- Aircraft
- SAMs
- AAA

A couple of bombers are returning from a long range mission.  Their fuel reserves are low, so we're sending out a KC-49 tanker to provide air-to-air refuelling.

We are concerned that enemy aircraft will intercept the tanker, which is where you and your wingmen come in.
fr: so we're sending out a KC-49 tanker to provide air-to-air refuelling.

en:
Fly with the tanker and keep it safe. Maintain active radar and RWR so you are aware of hostiles. 

AWACs will also be available to help spot incoming threats.
fr: Volez avec le petrolier et gardez-le en securite.�Maintenez le radar et le RWR actifs pour etre au courant des ennemis.

en:
SUMMARY
Objective: 
- Escort the tanker to the rendezvous.  
- Engage all hostile aircraft that approach.
- Mission complete when the tanker and bombers return to base.

Threats:
- Hostile aircraft

It's time to send a naval strike group deep into enemy territory.  The aircraft carrier and its escorts will soon be ready to depart, but enemy forces are close.  

They will likely attempt to stop the carrier group before our mission can even begin.

Your job is to protect the ships, onboard aircraft, and the naval base from the enemy attack.  Hostile aircraft and land vehicles are approaching.  

Once the coast is clear, you will land on the carrier and join on the offensive.

SUMMARY

Objective:
- Defend naval strike group and naval base

Threats:
- Fighter Aircraft
- Bombers
- Tanks
- Mobile Anti-Air

The carrier group's first stop is a small northern island territory occupied by the enemy.

They have a few military bases here and use the island to stage their attacks on our western coast.
fr: Le premier arret du groupe de porte-avions est un petit territoire insulaire du nord occupe par l'ennemi.

en:
The island is a valuable asset to the enemy's air and naval forces, so it's our duty to halt their operations here.

We will launch a full on air assault.
fr: so it's our duty to halt their operations here.

en:
There are 4 major components to the attack, which will be split up among 4 specialized air groups.

Whiskey group will suppress enemy air defenses. X-ray group will attack ground targets such as armored vehicles and supply depots.  Bravo will sink the enemy ships.
fr: which will be split up among 4 specialized air groups.

en:
Kilo group, your group, will fly combat air patrol and keep the enemy fighters away from the other groups.

The enemy only has a few groups of fighters in the air, but they have a carrier full of aircraft ready to go, and an airbase not far from our point of entry.
All groups will maintain open communications, but you will only have command over your own group.  Focus on your own objective (CAP) but maintain awareness of the bigger picture.
fr: but you will only have command over your own group.  Focus on your own objective (CAP) but maintain awareness of the bigger picture.

en:
SUMMARY

Objective:
- Combat air patrol

Targets:
- Multiple hostile aircraft

Threats:
- Hostile Aircraft
- SAMs
- Ships

We have located the enemy's main source of oil off the shore of some remote islands.  

The carrier group has been sent to destroy the oil platforms and further reduce the enemy's ability to fuel war.
fr: Nous avons localise la principale source de petrole de l'ennemi au large de certaines �les eloignees.

en:
There seems to be an unusually high naval military presence here, so the guided missile cruisers will be assisting your attack.

Air groups X-ray and Sierra will be primarily focused on SEAD, while Bravo will provide CAP.
fr: so the guided missile cruisers will be assisting your attack.

en:
Your group, Kilo, will be responsible for striking the oil platforms.

We need the platforms to be destroyed beyond all repair, so you can either destroy all key components on the platform, or destroy two support pillars to topple the entire platform.

Our cruisers will approach from the north, on the western side of the ridge. 

The air groups will approach on the eastern side of the ridge at low altitude. You should remain undetected until you reach the channel.
fr: on the western side of the ridge.

en:
The SEAD attack from the east should occur at the same time that the cruiser anti-ship missiles reach the enemy.

This will keep their defenses saturated while Kilo comes in to take down the oil platforms.
fr: L'attaque SEAD depuis l'est devrait se produire en meme temps que les missiles anti-navires des croiseurs atteignent l'ennemi.

en: There may be other ground targets for you, but we will keep you updated on those as we acquire more information.
fr: but we will keep you updated on those as we acquire more information.

en:
SUMMARY

Objective:
- Destroy 4 oil platforms

Threats
- Ships
- SAMs
- Aircraft

This mission will have two phases.
On the first phase, Kilo 1-1 will lead the flight into enemy territory.

You will be Kilo 1-2, and are assigned to support the flight lead.  Execute her commands to destroy secondary targets on the way to the enemy base.

The mission is scheduled to start when one of the enemy's coastal defense sites goes down temporarily.

We expect the defenses to resume operation when they spot your approach, but at least it will give you an opportunity to disable them before they can acquire you.
fr: La mission doit commencer lorsque l'un des sites de defense c�tiere de l'ennemi tombe temporairement en panne.

en:
The flight path will be low, weaving through the valleys to avoid line of sight with enemy radar.

Maintain formation with Kilo 1 for the entirety of the ingress phase.
fr: weaving through the valleys to avoid line of sight with enemy radar.

en:
The secondary targets are coastal defenses at Alpha and two IR SAM units at Bravo. Destroying them will help clear the way for the bomber. 

Again, flight leader Kilo 1-1 will call the shots on these targets.
fr: Les cibles secondaires sont les defenses c�tieres a Alpha et deux unites IR SAM a Bravo.�Les detruire aidera a degager la voie pour le bombardier.

en:
The primary objective will begin when you reach the base at Charlie.

Allied rocket artillery will be in the area launching strikes on the base's air defenses.
fr: L'objectif principal commencera lorsque vous atteignez la base de Charlie.

en:
The primary targets are rows of cylindrical tents lined up from east to west.

Your flight path will allow you to strike multiple targets in a single low-altitude bombing pass.
fr: Les cibles principales sont des rangees de tentes cylindriques alignees d'est en ouest.

en: After the first pass, flight lead duties will be passed over to you (Kilo 1-2).  Lead your wingmen to take down the remaining targets.
fr: flight lead duties will be passed over to you (Kilo 1-2).  Lead your wingmen to take down the remaining targets.

en:
A group of F-45A's will take off from a nearby FARP to help keep enemy aircraft and other threats off of you and your wingmen.

Once primary targets have been destroyed, an AV-42C will also dispatch from here to deliver troops to the headquarters and capture the enemy leaders.
fr: Un groupe de F-45A decollera d'un FARP a proximite pour aider a garder les avions ennemis et d'autres menaces hors de vous et de vos ailiers.

en:
You will be tasked to protect them at that time, but we'll update you on that final operation when we get to it.

Focus on supporting your wingmen during the flight through hostile territory and destroying the primary targets.
fr: but we'll update you on that final operation when we get to it.

en:
SUMMARY

OBJECTIVES
-  Clear air defenses for bombers
- *Destroy enemy assets
-  Protect troop transport

THREATS
- IR and Radar SAMs
- Aircraft
A small collection of quick missions for the F-45A.
fr: Une petite collection de missions rapides pour le F-45A.

en: Take the lead on this two-part mission to take down hostile bombers.
fr: Prenez la tete de cette mission en deux parties pour abattre les bombardiers hostiles.

en: Destroy the long range MAD-4 Radar (M4) near the airbase.
fr: Detruisez le radar MAD-4 a longue portee (M4) pres de la base aerienne.

en: Destroy the fighters taking off from the base with the help of India group.
fr: Detruisez les combattants qui decollent de la base avec l'aide du groupe indien.

en: Destroy bombers taking off from second airbase.
fr: Detruisez les bombardiers decollant de la deuxieme base aerienne.

en: Attack high value targets in an attack on enemy territory.
fr: Attaquez des cibles de grande valeur lors d'une attaque sur le territoire ennemi.

en: Locate and destroy the command & control bunkers
fr: Localisez et detruisez les bunkers de commandement et de contr�le

en: Destroy the artillery attacking our ships.
fr: Detruisez l'artillerie qui attaque nos navires.

en: Find and destroy the highly capable enemy stealth fighters.
fr: Trouvez et detruisez les combattants furtifs ennemis hautement capables.

en: Find and destroy the enemy bomber aircraft.
fr: Trouvez et detruisez les bombardiers ennemis.

en: Do not let the enemy destroy either of our carriers!
fr: Ne laissez pas l'ennemi detruire l'un de nos transporteurs !

en: Practice arrested or vertical landings on a moving carrier.
fr: Pratiquez les atterrissages arretes ou verticaux sur un porteur en mouvement.

en: Search for and destroy enemy weapon caches. Avoid detection or pay the price. Once they know where you are, they'll do anything to stop you.
fr: they'll do anything to stop you.

en: Find and destroy enemy weapon caches. Locations unknown.
fr: Trouvez et detruisez les caches d'armes ennemies.�Emplacements inconnus.

en: Return to and land on the helipad.

You will be the first to launch from the carrier.

Destroy the long range air defenses at the enemy coastal airbase Alpha first so that we can launch fighters.
fr: Vous serez le premier a lancer depuis le transporteur.

en: Once the air defenses are destroyed, CAP group India will launch from the carrier to help you clean up the enemy fighters.
fr: CAP group India will launch from the carrier to help you clean up the enemy fighters.

en:
After clearing the fighters, land at the FARP to reconfigure for a purely air-to-air role. You will be joined by another F-45 to take down the enemy bombers taking off from airbase Bravo.

SEAD group Romeo will launch from the carrier to disable the SAM sites at Bravo.
fr: land at the FARP to reconfigure for a purely air-to-air role. You will be joined by another F-45 to take down the enemy bombers taking off from airbase Bravo.

en: Destroy the two bombers from Bravo then return to carrier to complete the mission!
fr: Detruisez les deux bombardiers de Bravo puis retournez au porte-avions pour terminer la mission !

en:
Complete all of the objectives, then return to the assault carrier.

You can complete them in any order you choose.

There's a mix of hardened surface targets and air targets.
fr: then return to the assault carrier.

en:
Enemy rocket artillery have moved into range and have begun firing on our fleet from the other side of a mountain.

They have a low hit probability, but we must destroy them.
fr: L'artillerie de fusee ennemie est arrivee a portee et a commence a tirer sur notre flotte de l'autre c�te d'une montagne.

en: Enemy bombers have also been known to operate from this area. If they decide to deploy them against our assault fleet, they will be a high priority target.
fr: they will be a high priority target.

en: We have little intel on their whereabouts, but a handful of enemy stealth fighters are stationed by the bay and must be destroyed.
fr: but a handful of enemy stealth fighters are stationed by the bay and must be destroyed.

en: Finally, you must find the enemy command post and destroy the two bunkers. The bunkers will likely be adjacent to large supply tents.
fr: you must find the enemy command post and destroy the two bunkers. The bunkers will likely be adjacent to large supply tents.

en: Enemy bases are well defended, so use caution when operating near them.
fr: so use caution when operating near them.

en: The mission will be considered a failure if either of our carriers are destroyed.
fr: La mission sera consideree comme un echec si l'un de nos transporteurs est detruit.

en:
No objectives or enemies.

You will start at 300kts, 1000ft above two carriers.  Contact one of them to request clearance to land.
You are stationed at small FARP (forward arming and refueling point) near an enemy airbase.  Unfortunately, you only have enough supplies for one last sortie, and it's a tough one.
fr: you only have enough supplies for one last sortie

en: The mission is to destroy 3 enemy weapon caches.  We don't know exactly where they are, but they are most likely near air defenses.  Based on their radar emissions, we have estimated the positions of 4 sites.  The caches may all be at one site, or spread out between them.
fr: but they are most likely near air defenses.  Based on their radar emissions

en: You don't have any support on this mission.  No extra fuel, no rearming, no wingmen, nothing.  With scattered SAM sites and numerous enemy air patrols, the odds are stacked against you.  Use stealthy tactics to maneuver around the area and destroy the targets.

SUMMARY:
Objective:
  - Destroy the 3 weapon caches (supply tents)

Threats:
  - SAMs
  - Patrolling aircraft
Learn how to use the cannon, rockets, and targeting system.
Learn how to use the hover autopilot feature.
fr: Apprenez a utiliser la fonction de pilotage automatique en survol.

en:
Today we will be learning how to operate the AV-42C.

The start-up procedure is not very complicated, so let's jump in and get started.

The AV-42C is capable of equipping various weapons.  Today you will learn how to use the 30mm GAU-8 cannon, and the Hydra-70 unguided rockets.  You will also learn how to find and acquire targets using the TGP.
fr: and the Hydra-70 unguided rockets.  You will also learn how to find and acquire targets using the TGP.

en: Vertical flight can be tricky, but by using the hover autopilot, you can take off, hover, and land with ease.
fr: but by using the hover autopilot

We're in the final stages of the assault on the enemy base.

We have the enemy right where we want them -- a small valley within range of our artillery.

We'll begin firing rocket artillery and need you to scout out the enemy position to confirm their destruction.

Your job will be to clean up any targets that remain after the artillery barrage.
Once the main enemy battalion has been destroyed, we'll have you scout out and destroy a few other secondary targets to support our ground forces and clear the way for our bombers.
Your role is crucial in this final push towards victory. Good luck!
Practice taking off and landing in various locations.
Just follow each waypoint. Can you make each landing smoother or more efficient than the last?
Finish the mission by landing on the moving cruiser's deck.

Welcome!

I know you've been itching for a bit of action so I have a few tasks lined up for you today.

Let's get started.

A huge mountain range divides us from the enemy territory, so we usually don't get too much activity in the area.

Recently we began spotting small groups passing through and setting up small camps on our side of the ridge.

They appear to be setting up forward operating bases to service their VTOL capable attack aircraft.

They are still early in the preparation stage so we should attack now before they get too fortified.

We currently have positive intel on two camps.  We know where they are, and that they're only equipped with small arms, so this should be a breeze for you.

Their locations are available in the objective data.

After you clear out those sites, there will be one more matter we need to look into.  

We are aware of transport activity in the high mountain region so we'll have you go and perform some recon.  Be sure to bring enough fuel.

Absolutely never go beyond the mountain range and into the plains.

Beyond that point is the enemy territory which is heavily defended by long range air defenses and fighters.

Summary
 Objectives
 - Destroy all targets at sites A and B
 - Perform recon in the high mountains
 Threats
 - Small arms fire
- MANPADS

For this mission, you will need to act quickly and quietly.

The enemy plans to launch several groups of aircraft from their base.

Your objective is to destroy all of these aircraft before they take off.

You will be taking off from a forward arming and refueling point (FARP) about 30 miles from the target.

Fly low and make your way to the to the airbase undetected.

A bomber is inbound to land at the airbase.  After it lands, the enemy fighters will begin to take off.  

You will have this window to strike while all aircraft are still on the ground.
Beware that if they spot you before you are ready to attack, they may launch preemptively to defend themselves.

SUMMARY

Primary Targets:
- Landed aircraft

Threats:
- IR guided SAMs
- Small arms fire
- AAA

en: The F/A-26B is equipped with powerful forward facing radar. Learn how to use it to detect and track other aircraft.  Lock onto enemy targets to allow you to fire radar guided missiles.
fr: Le F/A-26B est equipe d'un puissant radar oriente vers l'avant.�Apprenez a l'utiliser pour detecter et suivre d'autres avions.�Verrouillez les cibles ennemies pour vous permettre de tirer des missiles guides par radar.

en:
One of the most abundant and dangerous threats to aircraft are Surface-to-Air Missiles (SAMs), most of which rely on radar to find and track targets.

Suppression of Enemy Air Defense (SEAD) operations neutralize or destroy these threats.
fr: most of which rely on radar to find and track targets.

en:
One method of performing SEAD involves destroying the radar used by the SAMs.

You will learn how to use the Anti-Radar Attack Display (ARAD) in conjunction with the AGM-88 weapon to locate, target, and destroy enemy radars.
fr: Une methode d'execution SEAD consiste a detruire le radar utilise par les SAM.

en: Introduction to the vehicle, and a general overview of the cockpit.
How to start up and shut down the AH-94.
Control the TADS with the TEDAC and use it to slave the gun.
Learn about the AH-94 and take a quick look at each of the components in the cockpit.
Learn the steps to properly start up the engines, spin up the rotor, and safely turn everything off.
Learn about the TADS, controlling it with the TEDAC, and steering the gun turret.
A collection of cooperative or freeflight scenarios for multiplayer.
Use cooperation and the advanced capabilities of the F-45A to complete various objectives.
Destroy bunkers and supply tents at enemy airbase.
Destroy the enemy unit on the way to attack our base.
Destroy the MAD-4 set up near base to allow our AWACS to deploy.
Fly strike missions off the Aircraft Carrier with your buddies.
Destroy the enemy's secret bunkers hidden in the caldera.
Destroy the mine laying ships parked in the bay.
Find and destroy all ships in the enemy carrier group.
Find and kill the enemy leadership hiding in the town.
Do not allow your carrier to be destroyed.

Your team of F-45 pilots have been tasked to carry out an attack against the enemy.

Use cooperation and the advanced capabilities of your aircraft to complete the mission.

The first objective is to destroy the enemy Mobile Air Defense units (MAD-4) which are stationed just outside of our airbase.

We can't deploy our AWACS until these air defenses are eliminated.

A convoy of tanks are on their way to our base.  They may be little more than a nuisance to you, but destroy them nonetheless.  If they reach the base they will likely start destroying our supplies and other assets.
At your discretion, complete the rest of the mission by finding and destroying the numerous hostile aircraft, and finally busting the bunkers and supply depots at the enemy base.

This is a freeflight scenario with no objectives.

A

The carrier strike group has arrived at the enemy's doorstep in the northern sea.

Launch with your wingmen and take on the various objectives.

The skies are covered by enemy patrols and air defense units.  

Split the responsibilities of CAP, SEAD and Attack among your team members and work together to complete the mission.
Each team gets 4x F/A-26Bs and 2x F-45As. First team to 24 points wins!
Quick dogfight match for F/A-26B with guns and heat seeking missiles (AIM-9). First team to 24 points wins!
6 vs 6 Kestrels!  This was originally to look for bugs relating to the AV-42C.
Rescue your soldiers from the enemy base and bring them back to your own. Each team will need to bring home 3 soldiers.
Bring the final soldier to homeplate!
Quick dogfight match for F/A-26B. First team to 24 points wins!
Destroy the ground targets at the enemy base before they destroy yours. Defend your own assets from the enemy attack.
Destroy bunkers and supply tents at the enemy airbase.
Destroy tents and bunkers at Outpost A.
Destroy tents and bunkers at Outpost B.
Destroy the ground targets at the enemy base before they destroy yours. Defend your own assets from the enemy attack. Low-tech weapons only.
Destroy bunkers and supply tents at the enemy airbase.
Destroy tents and bunkers at Outpost A.
Destroy tents and bunkers at Outpost B.
Each team gets 4x F/A-26Bs and 2x F-45As. Try out some pure air combat!
The bases are about 75 nautical miles apart, so you will be able to spread out and make use of BVR (beyond visual range) tactics.
The first team to score 24 kills wins.
You're in the merge!  Get ready for a fight!
Use your guns, missiles, and flares to achieve victory!
This is just a test scenario for the AV-42C.

The object of the game is to pick up and bring home 3 soldiers.

You will need at least one AV-42C on your team to complete the objectives.

Only one soldier will appear at a time.  Once you successfully bring home the soldier, a new one will appear in a different location.

Each new soldier will be closer to the enemy base.
The soldiers can't be killed.  If an AV-42C is shot down while carrying a soldier, the soldier will return to its spawn point.

This is a classic guns-only dogfight scenario. 

You will spawn head to head with your opponents.  

Prepare for combat!
Try to avoid shooting before the merge!
The first team to suffer 24 deaths loses.

In this scenario, each team has assets that they will need to defend, as well as enemy targets they need to destroy.

Work together with your team to attack and defend.

Team A is based in the north-western region, while Team B is in the south-eastern region.

Each team has 3 outposts which are the primary targets to attack/defend.

Larger scale missions designed for multicrew and multiple helicopters.
Spearhead the effort to liberate a city under enemy occupation.
Destroy or disable all MAD-4 units.
Disable the long range air defenses on the ships.
Find the makeshift HQ and destroy all of its major assets.
Destroy patrolling GAV-25 group, or let our fighters handle it.
Escort special forces unit Bravo to extract the civillians.
Destroy the armored units moving up the road towards our base.
Destroy the 3 APCs carrying the enemy dictators.
Find and destroy rocket artillery trucks.

The city has been overrun by the enemy. They've taken complete control and have set up a makeshift HQ at the city center.

Most of the civillians have been evacuated, however a small group is trapped in one of the industrial buildings.
Our main goal today is to get those civillians to safety, but there are a few steps we need to take in order to do that.

A pair enemy ground attack aircraft are patrolling the area.  They need to be destroyed before we can begin the rescue operation.

We would send in fighters to take care of them but the enemy have strong air defenses.

This is where you will begin.

Destroy the MAD-4 units around the city, as well as the long range anti-air missile systems on the ships parked off the coast.

This will allow us to send the fighters to gain air superiority.

Once the air defenses and air patrol are destroyed, special forces unit Bravo will enter the city by road vehicles.

You will need to provide close air support and clear their way through the city streets.

Finally, while we have you on station and are maintaining air superiority, we need you to find the HQ that the enemy has set up downtown.  They are storing valuable supplies and equipment there, so destroy everything you find.

SUMMARY
Objectives
1. SEAD (MAD-4 and ship SAMs)
 2. Destroy enemy aircraft (with help)
 3. Escort Bravo on rescue mission
 4. Find and destroy assets at enemy HQ
Threats
 - SAMs, infantry, attack aircraft

Tonight, we're taking on a daring but crucial mission.

It's time to stop enemy's reign of terror.

We'll be launching from the carrier at midnight.
The enemy leaders have been highly elusive, but thanks to our network of informants, we have intel that all of the top officials will be in Pike City to oversee an inspection of 5 new warships.

The city, and the harbor especially, are heavily defended, but we can't pass up this opportunity.

Move towards the harbor, delaying detection as long as possible.  The moment they know we're here, the leaders will attempt to flee the city.
The primary objective is to assassinate the leaders, who will be riding in 3 armored personnel carriers (APCs).
We are also aware that mobile artillery units, both land and sea, are ready to deploy when provoked, so we must find them and destroy them before they can fire on our ships.
Find and assassinate the leaders, destroy the artillery boats and trucks, then return to the carrier.

en: Welcome to the air-to-ground missile tutorial!
fr: Bienvenue dans le didacticiel sur les missiles air-sol�!

en: Air-to-ground missiles (AGM) are useful for precisely hitting light to medium armored ground targets
fr: Les missiles air-sol (AGM) sont utiles pour frapper avec precision des cibles au sol blindees legeres a moyennes

en: You will use the TGP to designate targets for the AGMs
fr: Vous utiliserez le TGP pour designer des cibles pour les AGA

en: These are small, laser-guided, anti-tank missiles
Since they home in on the laser point emitted by your TGP, you must maintain line of sight to the target until it hits
fr: you must maintain line of sight to the target until it hits

en: To fire it, designate a target using the TGP, point your aircraft at the target until the missile locks on, then pull the trigger to fire
fr: designate a target using the TGP

en: You can also switch the missile seeker's uncage mode to MANUAL, which will allow you to fire at targets off boresight
fr: which will allow you to fire at targets off boresight

en: In MANUAL mode, you hold the trigger to uncage the seeker, then press the weapon switch button to fire
fr: you hold the trigger to uncage the seeker

en: Try shooting the targets around the mission waypoint using the AGM-114
fr: Essayez de tirer sur les cibles autour du point de cheminement de la mission a l'aide de l'AGM-114

en: Remember, you need to maintain line of sight with your TGP in order to guide the missile to the target
fr: you need to maintain line of sight with your TGP in order to guide the missile to the target

en: Great! Now switch to the AGM-65
This is a larger, slightly heavier hitting anti-tank missile with a more advanced optical seeker
fr: slightly heavier hitting anti-tank missile with a more advanced optical seeker

en: With this type of missile, you do not need to maintain a lock on the target after you fire at it
fr: you do not need to maintain a lock on the target after you fire at it

en: The fire-and-forget capability allows you to fire at multiple targets in one pass, or take cover after firing
Try taking down the targets at the next waypoint and practice taking advantage of the fire-and-forget capability
fr: Essayez d'abattre les cibles au prochain point de cheminement et entra�nez-vous a tirer parti de la capacite de tir et d'oubli

en: Nice shooting!  This concludes the air-to-ground missile tutorial
fr: Belle prise de vue !�Ceci conclut le didacticiel sur les missiles air-sol

en: Welcome to the Radar tutorial for the F/A-26
fr: Bienvenue dans le tutoriel Radar pour le F/A-26

en: Today, you will learn how to use the radar to find and track other aircraft, as well as designate targets for air to air missiles
fr: you will learn how to use the radar to find and track other aircraft

en: The display shows you a compressed representation of the radar's 120 degree field of view
fr: L'ecran vous montre une representation compressee du champ de vision de 120 degres du radar

en: The displayed range can be adjusted using the R+ and R- buttons
fr: La plage affichee peut etre ajustee a l'aide des boutons R+ et R-

en: Press R+ repeatedly until the display is at max range
fr: Appuyez plusieurs fois sur R+ jusqu'a ce que l'affichage soit a la plage maximale

en: As the radar sweeps over other aircraft, they will be displayed as blue icons for friends and orange icons for foes
fr: they will be displayed as blue icons for friends and orange icons for foes

en: The left/right SCAN ANGLE can also be adjusted to allow the radar to scan more rapidly but in a smaller slice of the sky
fr: L'ANGLE DE BALAYAGE gauche/droite peut egalement etre ajuste pour permettre au radar de balayer plus rapidement mais dans une plus petite tranche du ciel

en: Now, you can slew the target designator using the joystick's thumb control
fr: you can slew the target designator using the joystick's thumb control

en: Slew the designator over a contact, and press in on the center of the thumb control to start tracking it
fr: and press in on the center of the thumb control to start tracking it

en: You can track up to 4 contacts while still being able to scan the rest of the sky
fr: Vous pouvez suivre jusqu'a 4 contacts tout en etant capable de scanner le reste du ciel

en: They will appear as small circle on your HUD, along with their corresponding number
In order to lock a target for weapons, click on a track again using the designator, or press the numbered MFD button on the left
fr: click on a track again using the designator

en: While a target is locked, the other tracks will continue to be displayed, but the radar will not be able to scan for new targets
fr: the other tracks will continue to be displayed

en: Information about the locked target's bearing, range, altitude, airspeed, and aircraft type will appear on the bottom right of the display
Use the UNLCK button to unlock the target, and the CLR button to clear the tracks
fr: and the CLR button to clear the tracks

en: For close in engagements, the radar can be switched to boresight mode using the MODE button
fr: the radar can be switched to boresight mode using the MODE button

en: In this mode, the radar will point straight forward and lock onto the first contact it sees
fr: the radar will point straight forward and lock onto the first contact it sees

en: If the radar is SOI, you can press the joystick thumb control to quickly unlock and find a new target
fr: you can press the joystick thumb control to quickly unlock and find a new target

en: Now for some weapons practice. Go back to scan mode and find, track, and lock the enemy aircraft.
Good. Now arm your weapon system and switch to the AIM-120
fr: Bien.�Armez maintenant votre systeme d'arme et passez a l'AIM-120

en: On the HUD, the locked target will appear as a small square.  The small dot is the shot lead cue
fr: the locked target will appear as a small square.  The small dot is the shot lead cue

en: When firing air to air missiles, aim for the lead cue to help the missile conserve energy as it steers toward the target
fr: aim for the lead cue to help the missile conserve energy as it steers toward the target

en: The DLZ is displayed on the right side of the HUD. The missile should be fired when the target chevron lies between the min and max marks
fr: Le DLZ est affiche sur le c�te droit du HUD.�Le missile doit etre tire lorsque le chevron cible se situe entre les marques min et max

en: By tracking multiple contacts, you can fire up to 4 AIM-120s on separate targets as long as you maintain line of sight with each of them
fr: you can fire up to 4 AIM-120s on separate targets as long as you maintain line of sight with each of them

en: When the AIM-120's time to impact counter displays the letter M, it has switched to active homing and you no longer need to track it.
fr: it has switched to active homing and you no longer need to track it.

en: Now, try shooting down the rest of the enemy air targets.
fr: try shooting down the rest of the enemy air targets.

en: Out of missiles!  You hit some of the targets though!
fr: Plus de missiles !�Vous avez atteint certaines des cibles cependant!

en: Out of missiles!  You didn't hit anything.  Want to try again?
fr: Plus de missiles !�Vous n'avez rien touche.�Vous voulez reessayer�?

en: SEAD stands for Suppression of Enemy Air Defenses
fr: SEAD signifie Suppression des defenses aeriennes ennemies

en: You will use a combination of radar detecting sensors and special weapons to disable SAM sites
fr: Vous utiliserez une combinaison de capteurs de detection radar et d'armes speciales pour desactiver les sites SAM

en: When a radar is searching for aircraft, it emits a signal that can be detected by your RWR
fr: it emits a signal that can be detected by your RWR

en: The radar type, bearing, and approximate range is shown on the RWR display, relative to your position in the center
This display shows the same information gathered by the RWR, but allows you to select targets for ARMs
fr: but allows you to select targets for ARMs

en: You can also set radar sources to be displayed as diamonds in the HUD
fr: Vous pouvez egalement definir les sources radar a afficher sous forme de losanges dans le HUD

en: When you lower the AR visor, you'll be able to see all of the targets around you for better situational awareness
fr: you'll be able to see all of the targets around you for better situational awareness

en: Now you can use your joystick thumb control to slew the targeting cursor
fr: Vous pouvez maintenant utiliser le contr�le du pouce de votre joystick pour faire pivoter le curseur de ciblage

en: Slew the cursor onto the enemy radar, then press in on the thumb control to set the target
fr: then press in on the thumb control to set the target

en: A square will appear on the selected target in both the MFD and the HUD
fr: Un carre appara�tra sur la cible selectionnee dans le MFD et le HUD

en: This is a high speed, fire-and-forget anti-radiation missile (ARM)
When fired, it will home in on the radar source designated in the ARAD
fr: it will home in on the radar source designated in the ARAD

en: Once you have a target selected, all you need to do is fly toward the target, and fire once the missile is in range
fr: all you need to do is fly toward the target

en: Try taking out the SAM radars using the AGM-88
fr: Essayez de retirer les radars SAM en utilisant l'AGM-88

en: Great!  This is the end of the SEAD tutorial.
fr: Genial!�C'est la fin du didacticiel SEAD.

en: Welcome to the AH-94 Attack Helicopter

Don't worry about memorizing everything now.
We'll go into more details in later sessions.
The AH-94 is a twin turboshaft attack helicopter with a tandem cockpit for two crew members.
It has a traditional rotor configuration of a large main rotor and small tail rotor.
The helicopter can be flown from either the rear pilot seat, or the front copilot gunner seat.
You can decide how to split up responsibilities.
Now, let's quickly go over each of the components in the cockpit.

Finally, and most importantly,
the flight controls...
Used to control weapons and sensors

This concludes the general overview of the AH-94 cockpit. 
You can move on to the next session to learn about how to get this thing started

Welcome back. 
In this session, we'll go over the start up and shut down procedures.
Before starting up, let's make sure everythings in the right state.
This will supply power to all of the aircraft's electrical components.
The engine starters use up a lot of power so we're gonna need the APU to keep the battery charged.
This system will spin up the turbine to a suitable RPM to begin combustion.
Running two starters can often overload the power supply so I'd start one at a time.
The starter  will run the turbine up to about 30% and automatically shut itself off.
Great, now both engines are fired up and running stable at idle.
You don't need to worry about applying the the proper throttle to maintain rotor RPM.
Just leave the power lever in the flight position and the system handles it for you.
At this point, the helicopter is ready to take off!
We can practice taking off and hovering in another session, so let's go over the shut down procedure.
And that's it!  This concludes the AH-94 start up and shutdown procedures.  See you next time.
Welcome!  Today we'll learn about the TADS and how to use the gun along side it.
To make things easy, we can do this all here on the ground so you don't have to worry about flying.
For this tutorial, let's turn on some hints so you can see what the controls do.
This will show labels when you grab the collective, cyclic, or TEDAC, and can be on or off at any time.
The primary targeting system is the TADS and you'll most often be using it on the TEDAC, which stands for TADS electronic display and contro
This works just like the TGP in the other vehicles except that the SOI controls are on the left hand.
While the TEDAC controls are held, use the left thumb control to slew the sensor, and the right thumb control to zoom in and out.
Switch weapons by using the thumb button on the right hand TEDAC control, and fire by using the right trigger.
Fire and switch weapons on cyclic.
Let's make sure that the gun is in slave mode, so the turret will point where we want it.
When the gun is slaved, it will either track to where your head is pointing, or to where the TADS is pointing, when the TADS is the SOI.
Use the TADS to find and designate the target on the range, and use the right trigger to fire.
Shoot the target to your left.
You can also set the TADS as SOI and enabled HEAD mode to have the TADS track your head, and display it's view in your HMD.
When in this mode, pressing in on the left thumbstick on the TEDAC will lock the TADS to where you've pointed it.
As you can see, the TADS and the Weapons can be controlled independently or in unison.
If you have a copilot, you or your copilot can take control of either system by using the SOI button and the master ARM button respectively.

You have control = RED
Copilot has control = YELLOW
Same functions as TEDAC R except trim

That's all for today!
Go practice!
